div.p:
The ſaid Diodorus related, that in a Colome or Pillar dedicated to this Idoll, was written theſe words; 
                        Ego Iſis ſum Egipti Regina, à Mercurio erudita, quae ego legibus ſtatui, nullus ſoluet; ego ſum prima frugū inuentrix, &c.

                     I am Iſis, the Queene of Egipt, taught by Mercurius, none ſhall diſſolue the lawes which I haue made, I am the firſt inuenter of cornes.
